If, one day, you must choose between rapid growth and trust — choose trust.
If you must choose between short-term profit and restoring the Earth — choose the Earth.
If you must choose between a closed ecosystem and open standards — choose openness.
If you must choose between complex technologies and real benefit for people — choose benefit.
In twenty years, the company will be judged by its valuation, the number of its facilities, its capitalization, or its influence on the global economy. But that was never the real goal.
